@@TJvCustomBehaviorLabel.Behavior
Summary
  Specifies a specific behavior for the label.
Description
  Use Behavior to select a specific effect for the label. You can select one of the following:
  
  * <LINK TJvLabelBlink,Blinking>: Blinks the text of the label.
  * <LINK TJvLabelBounce,Bouncing>: Bounces the label over the form.
  * <LINK TJvLabelScroll,Scrolling>: Scrolls the text of the label.
  * <LINK TJvLabelTyping,Typing>: Type effect: makes individual letters of the label appear one after each other.
  * <LINK TJvLabelAppear,Appearing>: Scrolls the label over the form.
  * <LINK TJvLabelSpecial,Special>: Makes individual letters of the label appear one after each other.
See Also
  BehaviorOptions
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomBehaviorLabel.BehaviorOptions
Summary
  Controls the specific behavior (special effect) of the label.
Description
  Use the properties of BehaviorOptions to alter the specific behavior of the label. You can specify
  a specific behavior for the label by setting property Behavior. Different special effect have different
  options. 
  
  For example if you set Behavior to 'Scrolling', you can use BehaviorOptions to alter the interval between
  scrolling events.
