@@TJvLabelAppear
Summary
  Enables the label to fly onto the form.
Description
  Use TJvLabelAppear to enable a TJvBehaviorLabel to fly onto the form. The label
  can be set to appear from the top, right, bottom or left side of the screen. The appearing
  sequence is handled in a background thread which makes it possible to have multiple labels
  appearing at the same time.

  When the label has appeared, the OnAppeared event is called.

  To use TJvLabelAppear capabilities with a TJvBehaviorLabel label, do the following:
  * Drop a TJvBehaviorLabel on a form.
  * Set <LINK TJvCustomBehaviorLabel.Behavior,Behavior> to 'Appearing'.
  Do the following with the properties of property <LINK TJvCustomBehaviorLabel.BehaviorOptions,BehaviorOptions>:
  * Use AppearFrom to specify the direction from which the label is to appear.
  * Set Delay to a interval in milliseconds before the label starts appearing.
  * Set Interval to a interval in milliseconds between two moves of the label.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelAppear.AppearFrom
Summary
  Indicates the direction from which the label is to appear.
Description
  AppearFrom indicates the direction from which the label appears on the form. You can specify if
  the should appear from the left (drFromLeft), the right (drFromRight), the top (drFromTop) or the
  bottom (drFromBottom) of the form.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelAppear.Delay
Summary
  The interval before the label starts appearing.
Description
  FirstInterval determines the initial delay (in milliseconds) before the label begins to move into
  view.
See Also
  AutoStart, Interval
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelAppear.Interval
Summary
  The interval between two moves of the label.
  Determines the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes before the label text is scrolled.
Description
  Interval indicates the delay (in milliseconds) between two stages of appearing.

  Interval determines how frequently the scroll event occurs. Each time the specified interval passes,
  the label text scrolls.

  Use Interval to specify any cardinal value as the interval between scroll events. The default value 
  is 50 (1/20 second).

  A 0 value is valid, however the label text will not scroll for a value of 0.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
